絵が小さい頃から得意で教室に飾ってもらったり県特選を頂いたり、カレンダーにも使っていただいたりしていたのですが…小学校卒業(図画工作の授業の終わり)を目処にその能力を伸ばすことを辞めてしまいました。大人になってやっと今頃、能力を捨てるのは勿体ないと気付き、まずは趣味から特技へ、特技から仕事(別に業務の一部に取り入れるだけでも良い)に変わる日が来ればいいなあとか思って始めたわけですが、そういう学校を出ていないし、少々弱気になってきました…
.

Purely digital art after so long! I'm trying to incorporate elements of my traditional art style into my digital style to improve the consistency between the two. For this practice, it was the visual style in general and the look of the lineart and shadows. Additionally, I practiced drawing varied characters and color palette choices.

"If you get in my way, we're gonna have a problem." Shanks is a character that reaches me on such a personal level. I love that a character who is easily one of the strongest in his world is also one of the kindest. He is also disabled, missing his left arm. Yet neither his disability nor his kindness are treated as weaknesses.
What is a character that sticks out to you? Who has stayed in your mind?
